                "National Laboratory."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Thin target foils (1.5 mg/cm2) were prepared by",
                "vacuum on high- purity gold (99.999%) from a hot",
                "tungsten wire onto high- purity radiochemically",
                "analyzed aluminum foil."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "DETECTOR": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "GEMUC",
                "PROPC"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                ""
              ]
            }
          ],
          "METHOD": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": [
                "CHSEP",
                "ACTIV"
              ],
              "free_text": [
                " Standard radiochemical procedures",
                "common to higher Z fission were used in this study,",
                "except that much higher levels of decontamination",
                "from extraneous spallation products were required.",
                "Measurements of radioactivity were carried out by",
                "beta counting in either low-background",
                "anticoincidence shielded Geiger counters or",
                "thin-window flow proportional counters."
              ]
            }
          ],
          "COMMENT": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Compiler's comment: Authors assume independent",
                "yields for 72Zn, 82Br and 96Nb. According to modern",
                "skeleton schemes 82Br and 96Nb are shielded nuclei",
                "while 72Zn is not shielded. Consequently, it is",
                "proper to move 72Zn (T1/2=46.5 HR) from independent",
                "to potentially cumulative yields."
              ]
            }
          ],
